
[1]jilt

   JILT, n. [of uncertain etymology.] A woman who gives her lover hopes
   and capriciously disappoints him; a woman who trifles with her lover.

   1. A name of contempt for a woman.

   JILT, v.t. To encourage a lover and then frustrate his hopes; to trick
           in love; to give hopes to a lover and then reject him.

   JILT, v.i. To play the jilt; to practice deception in love and discard
                                   lovers.
